# Pi-hole Custom DNS Entries
# Maps .ll domains to Nginx reverse proxy
# Nginx (172.20.0.2) routes requests to appropriate services on port 80
# These domains are accessible via VPN (WireGuard or Tailscale)

# ALL SERVICES ROUTE THROUGH NGINX REVERSE PROXY
# This allows clean URLs without port numbers (e.g., http://media.ll)

# Container Management
172.20.0.2 portainer.ll

# Photo Management (Immich)
172.20.0.2 immich.ll
172.20.0.2 photos.ll

# Media Streaming (Jellyfin)
172.20.0.2 jellyfin.ll
172.20.0.2 media.ll

# Document Management (Paperless)
172.20.0.2 paperless.ll
172.20.0.2 docs.ll

# Matrix Chat Server
172.20.0.2 matrix.ll
172.20.0.2 chat.ll

# Element Web (Matrix Client)
172.20.0.2 element.ll

# Pi-hole DNS
172.20.0.2 pihole.ll
172.20.0.2 dns.ll

# WireGuard VPN Management (only if using WireGuard)
172.20.0.2 vpn.ll
172.20.0.2 wg-easy.ll
172.20.0.2 wireguard.ll

# How it works:
# 1. Browser requests http://media.ll
# 2. DNS resolves to 172.20.0.2 (Nginx)
# 3. Nginx checks server_name and proxies to http://172.20.0.21:8096 (Jellyfin)
# 4. User sees Jellyfin without typing port numbers!
